<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">
Ahh the good times, Levels 34 to 50.  Perfect for an enchanter to charm solo.  As many people have mentioned there are many variations on the theme, but they all work given the right person and the right spot.<P>Few notes from my own experiences..<P>By charm soloing, I was able to gather xp so fast and by casting so little that I managed to level from 40 to 50 with a 30 point defecit in skill points for casting abilities.  Defense was maxxed, but at 54 I'm still at 205 in the odd skill.  This is good and bad of course.<P>Casting times:<BR>Beguile casts in the time a color shift stuns a pet.  Hit color shift, beguile - voila.  Cheap easy recharm.<P>Cajoling whispers does not fit in any of the Flux stuns.  I rediscovered mesmerize for holding (non-giants) still while recharming.  The same applies to Allure at levels 49 to 52.<P>At 53, you get Boltrans which does cast in the span of a shift.<P>At 51, many of the old haunts are beginning to green out to you.  Dreadlands is good still but it takes a while to find two blues amidst heaps of greens.  More running with the pet in tow lowers the effeciency.<P>Above 50 charm solo spots:<P>*warning* as you get above level 50, more and more things will /con blue to you.  Many Blue cons can summon.  (almost any level 50+ creature who has been damaged will summon)<P>Skyfire - great charming here.  Dead zones north of Overthere, and by BW zone.  Never Fight Chromodracs.<P>Trakanon's Teeth (51 and 52) - One spectral commander with sltw can solo any of the keeper camps.  <P>the Hole - the enterance can be cleared down to the rock golem/crusader spawn at the ramp.  If you can clear all 12 spawns in 20 mins, you're doing well.  If you're feeling bold, that rock golem can do the whole batch on his own.<P>Sebilis Enterance.  Everthing comes in pairs  <IMG SRC="http://forums.castersrealm.com/eq/smile.gif">  no place to zone though.<P>Wakening land.  The Sentinels are green/blue upto 53.<P>Cobalt scar.  Wyverns!  Giant flagged.<P>It's just plain NOT SAFE to charm solo in the western wastes, too many things summon.<P><BR>
</FONT>
