<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">
I like charm soloing anything that can be messed. This allows the stun, mes, root, or what ever to escape.<P>Your lineup for soloing with a giant is great, I do prefer to slow the other mob with my 50 mana version because it is very efficient, and makes the battle go by very quick. <P>Feedback I use with a pair of mobs that are identical and I want to keep the damage almost even.<P>I love the damage of a hasted pet, and having one eat through multiple mobs on one charm makes us feel great. I have yet to hand mine weapons though. I heard one enchanter that handed two gnoll whips to his pet, now that would be very exciting, having a former pet be able to continuously stun you while he kills you. <IMG SRC="http://forums.castersrealm.com/eq/smile.gif"><P>Longest pet I kept so far was 1.5hours. This was done with me and a druid. Druid snared the mob, then I tashed, charmed, hasted as he pulled target with snare, and my pet attacked. I would cast fear on the target and he would pull next one. I would call when charm broke and he would re-ensnare I would retash and recharm. Pulling caster mobs were faster kills, I never got hit once, and the exp was flying due to the damage output and constant pulling. I did get with a spell once or twice that night, but that was expected.<P>
</FONT>
