Mal,<P>I understand your reasoning for the blur being memmed, but the reason I'd go with a mez in place of it is simple.  Once it's mezzed, if you really need to blur to get out of things, go mem it.  Or just mez-med until you're recovered.<P>I've been caught WAY too many times with no mez available when I first started charm soloing, and I just had to say to myself:  "These spells will always be memmed.. always."<P>Color Flux<BR>Root<BR>Dazzle<BR>Tashania<P>Now the flux can actually be any of the stuns, and the mez can be downgraded, especially when using Cajoling, where I HAVE to mez in order to recharm the mob.  But the point is, I refuse to travel without these spells ready.   <IMG SRC="http://forums.castersrealm.com/eq/wink.gif"><P>Xornn
