<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">
Charm soloing is a great way to get experience. IT is also a lot of fun. However I do have some differing opinions with the above guide.<P>Giants are bad. It is FUN to solo giants using charm. And I do it a lot for the fun of it. However if I was truly after xp, and worried about dieing, I would not do giants. Giants run faster than the average mob, thus making you run farther for the recharm, adding more time to the recharm time. They cannot be mezzed, mez can save your butt countless times while charm soloing.<P>My general spell line up is...<P>discordant mind<BR>dazzle (for parking any extra that may wander over)<BR>mesmerization(when root and charm break around the same time, this helps a lot)<BR>tashania<BR>mesmerize (yup the first one)<BR>color shift<BR>color flux (for those quick move aways, this chain stun is perfect amount of time and not costly with mana)<BR>root (nothing more than the first root you get is needed)
