<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">
A little strategy I have hit upon with my<BR>level 15 enchanter charm soloing in Lavastorm<BR>is to deliberately charm a No Exp pet and<BR>send it against a low blue mob.  The<BR>green pet is easy to charm/recharm and is<BR>not to terribly dangerous.  The twist in my<BR>method is that I WANT my pet to die.  I <BR>charm the pet, send it agains the nearest<BR>blue mob.  Make sure to root the blue mob<BR>at all times and then debuff the blue mob<BR>enough so that he kills my pet but is seriously damaged himself.  I then nuke the<BR>mob to death for full xp after he has killed<BR>my pet.  So the fight ends with 1 full exp<BR>kill and no charmed pet to worry about.  You<BR>then grab the nearest green mob and do it<BR>again.  This only is good in zones with<BR>plenty of green/low blue mobs to grab.<BR>Worst case scenario is you have a green mob<BR>and a slowed blue mob after you at once.<BR>This is not that hard to handle and you<BR>can get by without the SoW.<P>Guille<BR>15th Enchanter Innoruuk
</FONT>
