<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">
As with all XP farms, the KEY is lvl vs hp.<BR>Lvl is the PRIMARY thing factor in experience, followed by location. Nothing else matters. Mobs with high HP for level (giants)=more mana expended/longer time to kill=more downtime=less xp. Basically, giants SUCK for XP. The idea is to kill mobs that are high level, with low XP. Happ in butcherblock is a perfect example of this, about 800hp on a lvl 35 mob, which means she takes half the mana to kill.<BR>-Malk
</FONT>
