<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">
Great guide.  I soloed 42-47 in a very similar way in BW.  The one thing I do different, and I seem to be the only enchanter who does it, is rarely use root!  My line up was:<P>Mez<BR>Tash<BR>Charm (CW)<BR>Celerity / Fear (cant remenber name sonce I retired)<BR>Disco<BR>Entrance<BR>Invis<BR>Rune III<P><BR>I try and charm the highest pet that I can keep reasonably controlled - eg Scoriae hornets at 45+. I open with mes, tash, charm, speed.  Then I sit and swap speed for fear.  Then I just keep mowing thru stuff until my pet is ready to be killed.  When I fight stuff I usually fear (occasionally slow if mobs are wondering by).  In most Kunark, Velious zone mobs just zig zag and dont run far.  If charm breaks I entrance the target, then run and get some distance, then mes and recharm my pet.  When mes breaks I juts /pet attack to break the entrance and away be go again.
