<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">
FYI there's two other great undercon giants in EW.  Wardon somethingorother at the prizons and the Frost Giant Captain. The Frost Giant Captain is always 45 th lv. so this is good if you are high lv, and I've yet to see him capmed whereas the Wardon is almost always camped, and the two Kael guards are frequently camped.  The Capain also seems a bit tougher than the guards, I used him for hours the other day (well mostly running away, but hey.) and charms about the same as a lv 45 guard.  <P>You find the captain at the giant fort.  If he isn't out standing by the two savage guards he will usually be in the right building near the entrance.  this is the best spot to find him.  If he's in a building you charm one of the savage guards, and kill the other, then kill the one you charmed.  Then you can pull the captain alone from inside.  If he's standing betwen the two savages, then it's a bit tougher, and I'll leave it to you to figure out a way, because mine haven't been that great.  <P>The only thing to worry about with him is that you will run out of mana.  I found that if you just root him and mem blur he will go back, you can med up and go get him all over again, usually with full or close to full health.  If you are lucky, he will even just stand where you blurred him for about 5 min. waiting patiently for you to recharm him.  I've even occasionally had him just stand there and wait when a charm broke.<P><P>------------------<BR>-Justi Saurane 45 Erudite Enchantress, Worshiper of Quellious the Tranquil, of Brell Serlis Guild Leader of Ancient Hands.  Previously Justisaurane 36 Barbarian Shaman, 3 rd Hammer of the Tribrunal member of Valorblade<BR>- When trouble arises and things look bad, there is always one individual who perceives a solution and is willing to take command. Very often, that individual is crazy.
