<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">
I'm glad some folks are getting use out my guide. I know some people have additions, changes, etc. but that guide is just what worked for me.<P>Just a few points -<P>If you are charming indoors, I'd probably not haste the pet. You are relying on stuns to get your recharm on and you're asking to be hit. Your haste will eventually work against you. Outside tho, you should almost never get hit (your pet is never near you). Haste away.<P>I also know I get a heck of a lot more xp than when grouped. Even in a dam good group. The damage output I get for my mana is unparalleled. <P>Today I had one giant go for 8 kills before he broke charm (coincidentally, I was recasting it anyway because he had gone so long charmed - just as he broke, my spell finished and he was recharmed  <IMG SRC="http://forums.castersrealm.com/eq/smile.gif"> ).<P>The very next giant was a complete nightmare breaking charm every 30 seconds it seemed. <P>It goes both ways I guess.<P>One thing you can say tho - its NOT boring  <IMG SRC="http://forums.castersrealm.com/eq/smile.gif"><P>cheers<BR>Ig<BR>
</FONT>
