Just for hoots, I've been getting a little adventurous with this charming stuff. The last two nites (with about a half hour to play each), I solo'ed the entire Giant fort in Eastern Wastes.<P>The simple recipe was to charm the Frost Giant Captain (who ended up being the last kill), hasting him and slowing the other FG's. They can all be solo pulled.<P>All in all, I could kill 9 giants (counting the captain). All yielded XP and the hasted Captain was the only pet. The first time charm broke twice but with almost no burp in the action regaining control. The second time it was a bit more annoying. <P>I ended both battles with 40% mana or more.<P>Sorry.. maybe bragging a bit, but i'm trying to think up the next challenge. I'm working on indoor charming. <P>Its far tougher because getting hit is part of the game. Resisted stuns are dam dangerous (whereas resisted roots just mean more running).<P>Anyone have tactics for indoor (that arent obvious)?<P>Igbert<BR>50th chanter<BR>Rodcet
