<HR size="1" color="#dedfdf">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">
Igbert,<P>I loved the area that you suggested for levels 38-44. Iceclad rocks. All enchanters of the correct level should go there if they are looking to optimize their leveling time.<P>However, I am finding Eastern Wastes to be ... harder. Much harder. In Iceclad, it is not difficult to gain a a level is as low as 4 hours. However, I have YET to gain a level in the eastern wastes.<P>In have noted the following problems wrt. charm soloing in eastern wastes:<P>1. The Guard giant mobs are FAST. They are not full SoW speed, but I would guess that they are close to JBoot speed. This combined with the longer casting time of Cajoling Whispers, makes your root technique one of the few that have any chance at success. Sadly, the variable time of root means that your pet may be rooted for a consideriablt percentage of your root time.<P>2. Snow Griffons. They ABOUND near the entrance of Kael. They have to be one of the most leathal MOBs I have ever seen. Faster than SoW, social, moderate argo radius. I have no idea what verant was thinking with these MOBs (other than: NO MORE KITING IN THIS ZONE). I keep Gate Mem'ed just for this MOB. As soon as I see it engage my pet I am gone, and that adds a lot of the average kill time. <P>3. Sparse blues. The blues in this zone while plentiful, are rather sparse. By that I mean it can be a 30 second or more run from one blue to the next. As well all know, it is not a lot of fun to be running through a zone with a killing machine right behind you with nothing to throw it at!<P>4. Guard Magic Resistance. It would seem that the guards now have relativly high MR. Even after hitting them with tashania, they seem to break more often than the good old Scouts I used to love charming! Perhaps it is only an illusion. With the old scouts, when they broke it was a simply matter of running a little ways and then charming. Now we have to run, root the thing that is being fought (if it broke root), then we have to root the giant, then we have to charm the giant, and THEN we have to (somehow) get the two fighting again! This takes SERIOUS time.<P>Perhaps the zone has been tweaked recently. I don't know what to say other than DOH! <P>perhaps mezable MObs are the way to go??<BR>
</FONT>
