<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">
Good write up, and as everyone else I have my own strats to add..<P>First off, I personally prefer to do the Charming Indoors, and also prefer to Group rather then solo if I have the chance ;) <P>But anyway, Charm soloing is a blast, and certainly worth it once you understand the rules and regulations of staying alive..<P><BR>Indoor hints.<P>- Lev 4 Mes = GOD.<P>Unless you are on giants the level 4 mes will be your lifeline, its Almost never resisted, almost impossible to interrupt and only lasts for 20some seconds.. Plenty of time to recover after a Broken charm..<P>- CasterPets, Wizards Absolute best.<P>Charming casters as your pets is IMHO the absolute best way to keep yourself alive down in a dungeon. <P>First point: They unleash Massive damage as they have our_mana_pool^5. Ie, C2 your jin wizzie! (Lower level wizzie can kill higher meelee who is slowed without much problem)<P>Second reason why I prefer Caster pets. They SOSO love to cast mid delay MR based nukes when they break. If you can't resist a force shock, shame on you! while he's casting his 5sec nuke, he's not trying to hit you for double 120's<P>Overall strat:<P>Lev4 mes Castermob, Tash, Charm, C2, Aug if you're bored and feeling frisky.<P>Pull target mob will Slow, Tepid or forlorn, depending on mana availability..<P>Root target mob<P>/pet own !<P>Berserk pet if needed.. If charm breaks, MES it.. other is rooted, bam, no problem at all..<P>Essentially a safe way to do it..<P><BR>Another tactic possible for Soloing without charm. Mes, Fear, Nuke, Mes, Nuke :)<P>Great for keeling caster mobs ala highkeep/cindereela<P><BR>Vsai 57th enc<BR>Xegony.
</FONT>
